pe.  New political philosophies emerged, including Machiavelli's *The Prince*, which explored the acquisition and maintenance of power.  The Age of Exploration began, with European powers venturing across the oceans and establishing global trade networks.\n\nThe Renaissance was not a uniform movement across Europe; its impact varied across different regions and social groups.  However, its emphasis on humanism, reason, and artistic innovation laid the foundation for the Scientific Revolution and the Enlightenment, profoundly shaping the course of Western civilization."
